fmann told The Guardian.</p> <p>Stewart Thorndike, a New York-based filmmaker and friend of Hoffmann’s, <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/14/magazine/gaby-hoffmann-the-eloise-of-the-chelsea-hotel.html?pagewanted=all&amp;_r=0\">wrote the Leah character for Hoffmann</a>. Thorndike and producer Alex Acharfman decided to post the film online for free on 4 August to support Thorndike’s trifecta of female-driven horror films. Lyle will be online for the duration of a Kickstarter campaign that seeks to raise money for The Putney School, the second film in Stewart’s trio, which is about a haunted TED talk.<br /></p> <p>Hoffmann spoke to the Guardian from a television shoot in Los Angeles for the Amazon series <a href=\"http://www.vulture.com/2014/02/jill-soloway-on-her-amazon-pilot-transparent.html\">Transparent</a>, a comedy-drama which follows a family after the patriarch comes out as transgender. It’s the latest project for a one-time child star (Field of Dreams, Sleepless in Seattle) who as an adult has cemented herself as a classic independent film star with roles on television series Girls and films like Crystal Fairy and The Magic Cactus.<br /></p> <p>Hoffmann said she last saw a horror film when she was a kid, but chose the role because of the challenges it presented for her as an actress.<br /></p> <p>“I’m not that interested in horror films, I never have been. I don’t quite get the appeal,” Hoffmann said. “But as an actress, it seemed like a really, fun, juicy role to take on and it really was – I had a lot of fun making it, certainly.”<br /></p> <p>Most of the film was shot in one building, in five days. “You’re sort of in that world 24/7,” Hoffmann said. “You’re living breathing, eating it. It’s exhausting, but I kind of enjoy working that way, because you sort of merge with this false reality that you are trying to create.”<br /></p> <p>While Hoffmann enjoys the intense, problem-solving environment low budget films offer, she’s open to good storytelling on any level.<br /></p> <p>“What I prefer is good writing and smart people,” Hoffmann said. “Wherever that is found, and that is found all over the place in terms of budget, that’s where I tend to want to be.”</p>","headline":"Lyle: the 'lesbian Rosemary's Baby' to be streamed for free online","trailText":"Horror comedy stars Gaby Hoffmann as pregnant woman who goes into a paranoid fantasy when her first child dies","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/7/30/1406739355511/9da36277-b3cc-4fb3-bf2a-7a5c058ea767-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"427","commentable":"true","byline":"Amanda Holpuch","productionOffice":"US","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-08-02T13:00:00-04:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/jul/30/lyle-horror-comedy-gaby-hoffman-online-free","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/filmblog/2014/jul/30/lyle-horror-comedy-gaby-hoffman-online-free","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/filmblog","webTitle":"Film blog","type":"blog","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/filmblog","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"film/film","webTitle":"Film","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/film","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/film","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"us-news/us-news","webTitle":"US news","type":"keyword","sectionId":"us-news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/us-news","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/us-news/us-news","sectionName":"US news","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","sectionName":"Culture","references":[]},{"id":"film/horror","webTitle":"Horror","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.c